Docker Volume is a storage area outside the container where data is kept permanently.


  Key point to remember
Without a volume: Data is stored only inside the container and is lost if the container is removed.
With a volume: Data written to the mounted folder is stored in the Docker volume on the host, so it survives container deletion.
  Step 1: Create a volume
     docker volume create grafana-data
     docker volume ls
  Step 2: Attach the volume to the container
    docker run -d \
    --name grafana \
    -p 8080:3000 \
    -v grafana-data:/var/lib/grafana \
    grafana/grafana 

